RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (QUARTER HORSE RACE 1 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 78. Claiming Purse 8000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since July 2 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $2,500 (Maiden And Claiming Races For $2,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).

CLAIM.OWNER: Garcia Jose Eligio and Rivera Sally

RACE.FOOTNOTES: WATER'S FOR FIGHTN bumped by inside rival at the start, sent to vie for lead two wide on the backstretch, continued two wide on the turn, edged away late on the turn, entered lane clear, kept to task in the lane and safely held. OMAHA RUTSCH tracked pair of rivals two wide on the backstretch, continued two wide on the turn, launched bid three wide in the lane and closed best of rest to be second. MACHO SAM came out and bumped rival at the start, wanted to show speed but lacked room and rider took up on heels exiting the chute, went to rail to save ground tracking pair of leaders, continued along the rail on the turn, launched bid in between rivals but lacked needed punch to threaten top two. NOT GONNA LAST antsy and lifted in the gate, had head turned and came away last, stayed off the rail on the backstretch, asked and advanced in the three path through the turn, entered lane widest and made mild progress after the long sustained run. STANFORD GRAD vied for lead along the inside, continued along the inside on the turn, entered lane in range of leader, kept on until finally wilting in the final sixteenth. MISSING MAURICE antsy in the gate due to inside rival, off bit slow, settled off the pace off the rail on the backstretch, continued off the rail on the turn, and lacked needed response in the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Macho Sam
ENTRY.COMMENT: came out/bumped start, on heels early, tracked inside, mildly
